Package utilities

Class CartesianVector

java.lang.Object
utilities.CartesianVector
public class CartesianVector extends Object
A class for creating and working with 2D and 3D vectors Each instance contains an x, y, and optionally a z value, along with various functions for performing standard math operations on itself.
Author:
Icarus Innovated

    • getAddition

      public CartesianVector getAddition(CartesianVector a)
      Gets the result of adding another vector to the parent vector. This function does NOT modify the parent vector.
      Parameters:
      a - The vector to add to the parent.
      Returns:
      A new vector containing the result of the addition. The result will be the same type as the parent (2D or 3D).

    • getSubtraction

      public CartesianVector getSubtraction(CartesianVector a)
      Gets the result of subtracting another vector from the parent vector. This function does NOT modify the parent vector.
      Parameters:
      a - The vector to subtract from the parent.
      Returns:
      A new vector containing the result of the subtraction. The result will be the same type as the parent (2D or 3D).

    • getMultiplication

      public CartesianVector getMultiplication(double scalar)
      Gets the result of multiplying the parent vector by a number. This function does NOT modify the parent vector.
      Parameters:
      scalar - A double that will be used to multiply each component of the parent vector
      Returns:
      A new vector3D containing the result of the multiplication. The result will be the same type as the parent (2D or 3D).

    • getDivision

      public CartesianVector getDivision(double scalar)
      Gets the result of dividing the parent vector by a number. This function does NOT modify the parent vector.
      Parameters:
      scalar - A double that will be used to divide each component of the parent vector.
      Returns:
      A new vector3D containing the result of the division. The result will be the same type as the parent (2D or 3D).

    • getNormalization

      public CartesianVector getNormalization()
      Gets the result of normalizing the parent vector to a length of 1. This function does NOT modify the parent vector. Calling this function also updates the parent vector's magnitude.
      Returns:
      A new vector3D with the same direction as the parent, but with a length of 1. The result will be the same type as the parent (2D or 3D).

    • normalize

      public void normalize()
      Normalizes the parent vector to a length of 1. This function DOES modify the parent vector. Calling this function also updates the parent vector's magnitude.

    • magnitude

      public double magnitude()
      Calculates magnitude of the parent vector.
      Returns:
      A double representing the magnitude of the parent vector. This value is also stored in the parent to avoid extra calculations when possible.

    • direction

      public double direction()
      Calculates the direction of the parent vector.
      Returns:
      A double representing the direction of the parent vector in radians. This value is also stored in the parent to avoid extra calculations when possible.

    • average

      public double average()
      Calculates average of the parent vector's components.
      Returns:
      A double representing the average of the parent vector's components. This is only useful in a few cases, so ensure this is the right function. This value is also stored in the parent to avoid extra calculations when possible.
